<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="292" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1108,1603]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,414,1144,1170]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Material examined</emphasis>
:— 
<collectingCountry box="[447,554,1144,1170]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">BRAZIL</collectingCountry>
. Pantanal dos Marimbus,Andaraí, 
<collectingRegion box="[937,1067,1144,1170]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Bahia State</collectingRegion>
. Sample: 
<collectionCode box="[1173,1262,1144,1170]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15506" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15506" name="Universidade Estadual de Feira de Santana" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" type="Herbarium">HUEFS</collectionCode>
185370, 
<collectionCode box="[1363,1452,1144,1170]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15506" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15506" name="Universidade Estadual de Feira de Santana" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" type="Herbarium">HUEFS</collectionCode>
185390.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1108,1603]" box="[189,864,1216,1243]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,281,1216,1242]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Habitat</emphasis>
:—It was found on 
<taxonomicName box="[499,709,1216,1242]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lentibulariaceae" genus="Utricularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliosa">
<emphasis box="[499,709,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Utricularia foliosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(periphyton).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1108,1603]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,245,1252,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Note</emphasis>
:— 
<materialsCitation country="French Guiana" location="South America" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" specimenCount="1">
This variety, probably endemic to 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:6F25BE4935030D335EE5885845A1F9CE:E253598435030D335CCF88B04275FB72" box="[674,845,1252,1278]" country="French Guiana" name="South America" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">South America</location>
, is characterized in having rounded semicells, closed sinus, cell wall locally remarkably thickened and ornamented by scrobicles. Regarding this latter morphological feature, Thérezién reported scrobicles only at the central protuberance and the margins. In the Brazilian specimens, the whole cell wall is ornamented by those scrobiculations, and the cells are slightly longer. The 
<taxonomicName box="[1177,1363,1361,1387]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" rank="variety" variety="incrasstaum">
var. 
<emphasis box="[1226,1363,1361,1386]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">incrasstaum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite rare and till now it was only known to its 
<typeStatus box="[603,651,1397,1423]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">type</typeStatus>
locality in 
<collectingCountry box="[778,947,1396,1422]" name="French Guiana" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1108,1603]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">
Another 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Corda ex Ralfs" authorityYear="1848" box="[293,424,1432,1458]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Cosmarium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" phylum="Charophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[293,424,1432,1458]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Cosmarium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxon which was apparently endemic to that country was recently reported also in the Marimbus, 
<collectingCountry box="[267,340,1468,1494]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Therezien (1985: 85)" authorityName="Therezien" authorityPageNumber="85" authorityYear="1985" box="[353,1105,1468,1495]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Cosmarium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" phylum="Charophyta" rank="variety" species="anisochondrum" variety="isthmolatum">
<emphasis box="[353,667,1468,1494]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Cosmarium anisochondrum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[727,865,1468,1494]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">isthmolatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Therezien, Y." box="[874,1105,1468,1495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" pagination="5 - 275" refId="ref5633" refString="Therezien, Y. (1985) Contribution a l'etude des algues d'eau douce de la Guyane Francaise (a l'exclusion des Diatomees). Bibliotheca Phycologica 72: 5 - 275." type="journal article" year="1985">Thérézien (1985:85)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ramos, G. J. P. &amp; Santos, M. &amp; Moura, C. W. N." box="[1122,1339,1468,1494]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" refId="ref5485" refString="Ramos, G. J. P., Santos, M. A &amp; Moura, C. W. N. (2021) How hidden is the diversity of the genus Cosmarium (Desmidiaceae) in the Brazilian Caatinga? Acta Botanica Brasilica. [in press]" type="book" year="2021">
Ramos 
<emphasis box="[1211,1270,1468,1494]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
). Overall, there are other rare desmids co-occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[635,802,1504,1530]" name="French Guiana" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[857,928,1504,1530]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, especially in the Chapada Diamantina region, such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Therezien (1985: 82)" authorityName="Therezien" authorityPageNumber="82" authorityYear="1985" box="[223,916,1540,1567]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Euastrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" phylum="Charophyta" rank="variety" species="subcyclopicum" variety="elongatum">
<emphasis box="[223,504,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Euastrum subcyclopicum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[558,676,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">elongatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Therezien, Y." box="[682,916,1540,1567]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" pagination="5 - 275" refId="ref5633" refString="Therezien, Y. (1985) Contribution a l'etude des algues d'eau douce de la Guyane Francaise (a l'exclusion des Diatomees). Bibliotheca Phycologica 72: 5 - 275." type="journal article" year="1985">Thérézien (1985: 82)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ramos, G. J. P. &amp; Costa, F. M. &amp; Santos, M. A. &amp; Moura, C. W. N." box="[930,1138,1540,1566]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" pagination="185 - 196" refId="ref5352" refString="Ramos, G. J. P., Costa, F. M., Santos, M. A. &amp; Moura, C. W. N. (2019) Taxonomic novelties, new records, and rare species of desmids from the Chapada Diamantina region, Brazil. Phytotaxa 391 (3): 185 - 196. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 391.3.2" type="journal article" year="2019">
Ramos 
<emphasis box="[1015,1071,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). However, more studies are recommended to investigate such similarity between the desmid flora of those two countries.
</paragraph>
